## Steps

1. [connect to raspberry pi through SSH by opening the command prompt on workstation and entering the command: ssh pi@pihole.local]  
2. [ensure the raspberry pi is up-to-date by entering the command: [sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y]
3. [to mount uptime Kuma, node.js must be installed on device. enter the command: curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs]
4. [installed uptime Kuma by entering the command: sudo npm install -g uptime-kuma]
5. [start uptime Kuma by entering the command: uptime-kuma | set uptime Kuma to auto start on reboot by entering the commmands: 
   sudo npm install -g pm2
   pm2 start uptime-kuma
   pm2 startup
   pm2 save ]
6. enter admin panel by entering http://)(private ip):3001 and make necessary changes to settings.

